node.text: Like everyone around the country I’ve been blown away by the hard work of the NHS at the moment. To show my support and try to raise a few quid, I’m doing the only thing I know how and jumping on my bike. I’ll be doing three 12 hour shifts on Zwift, starting at 7:30am on Wednesday, Thursday and Friday. You’ll be able to ride alongside me on Zwift and also watch me live, suffering in my garage 🙈 I hope people will be able to make even the smallest donation to a great cause and hopefully a few of you will come and ride with me. Anyone fancy doing the whole 36 hours?! You can find out more at the donation link in my bio #GsNHSZwiftShifts #StayHomeStaySafe #prayformygooch

node.text:
So, no medal this year. It was always going to be tough out there. Congrats to @primozroglic, @tomdumoulin90 and @rohandennis 👏

But every Olympics is special, and to be here competing for @teamgb after the last 18 months everyone has lived through was an honour. Now it's time to get home to the family and then come back fighting 👍

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Geraint Thomas in Tokyo, Japan with @olympics, @teamgb, and @britishcycling. May be an image of one or more people, bicycle and outdoors.

node.text: Five years ago in Rio. Time to do it all again tomorrow in Tokyo. The road here hasn’t been the smoothest 🤦‍♂️ But I’m ready to give it everything I’ve got. Big thanks to @britishcycling and everyone back home for the support 🇬🇧🏴󠁧󠁢󠁷󠁬󠁳󠁿

The #StrongerTogetherChallenge is in full swing and looks like it’s getting pretty competitive... Maybe a few more steps might help me loosen up after my crash, before Wednesday’s TT.  Check the link in my bio to walk with me in my last days in Tokyo... 

#StrongerTogetherChallenge 

#Tokyo2020 

#DoWhatYouCant 

#Samsung 

#ad
